Azer plate, made for Mith Baruk dwarves through contract by Lord Galdor the Gold of Benzor. Though any good dwarf may use it. It is epic, and not of this plane. Only the greatest of warriors many even wear it correctly, or activate the magics within.

It is designed to be used with amulet also made for the leaders of the Mith Baruk by the Azer. Massive energy has been spent designing and planning the manufature of these items. It is obvious Lord Galdors charisma and reach is far beyond what most imagine.
This is magical, but unmarkedly so. However, in the hands of a skilled fencer, it can be quite powerful. Most often two are wielded at at once. It is made specifically for those that use the rapier.

Designed for the dwarves of the Mith Baruk. Under contract by the Azer, and specifically asked by Lord Galdor to construct such a device for those that lead the Mith. This powerful amulet allows good dwarves to become as Azer, immune to fire. It is epic in design, a kingly sum to purchase.

This ultimate weapon is made by the Azer. It is epic in stature, and can only be obtained with huge amounts of gold from an Azer truely skilled in weapon manufacture. It is made for those rare fighters that choose the stave.
